HEADWORD: Cation
<hw>Cat"i*on</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ downward +
<?/ going, p. pr. of <?/ to go.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>a
positively charged atom, radical, or molecule, which in electrolysis
migrates to the cathode; a positive <isa>ion</isa>; -- opposed to
<contr>anion</contr>.</def> <rj><au>Faraday.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
